INSERT INTO FILM_PERSON (ID, HEIGTH_CM, TRIVIA, BIOGRAPHY, NACIONALITY, ROL) 
VALUES (14, 170, 'Is the first director to have directed both a Star Trek film and a Star Wars film.', 'Jeffrey Jacob Abrams was born in New York City and raised in Los Angeles, the son of TV producer parents. At 15, he wrote the music for Don Dohler''s Nightbeast (1982). In his senior year of college, he and Jill Mazursky teamed up to write a feature film, which became Taking Care of Business (1990). He went on to write and produce Regarding Henry (1991) and Forever Young (1992). He also co-wrote Gone Fishin'' (1997) with Mazursky. Along with other Sarah Lawrence alumni, he experimented with computer animation and was contracted to develop pre-production animation for Shrek (2001).', 233, 99);

INSERT INTO FILM_PERSON (ID, HEIGTH_CM, TRIVIA, BIOGRAPHY, NACIONALITY, ROL) 
